  "note": "The training corpus REGISTRY + a graded CURRICULUM. `sources` is the declarative list of everything the creature can read (each with a stable `id`); `stages` groups sources into a math/science-first ladder and attaches a WORKSHEET pass-mark. Training advances a stage only when the creature SITS the stage's worksheet and passes (mastery-gated). Grounded (`generated`) sources carry the picture/tap channel -> clean facts the worksheet can grade; the maths and science worlds are modelled on what primary-grade arithmetic and elementary-science books actually teach. `gutenberg` books are US public domain and add reading/language (no worksheet). Grow the corpus by appending sources; grow the curriculum by editing stages. Fact sources render each triple through one of several paraphrase `frames` (P9 label discipline: the relation label never reaches the stream; the learner unifies the constructions; the label grades the worksheet).",
